From: Seeed Studio <support@seeed.cc>
Date: Fri, 23 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/rockchip: dw-mipi-dsi2: set panel orientation before device
 registration

When a DSI panel driver (e.g. ili9881c) calls
drm_connector_set_panel_orientation() from its get_modes callback, the
DRM device is already registered.  This triggers a WARNING in
__drm_mode_object_add():

  WARNING: CPU: 6 PID: 258 at drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mode_object.c:45
  __drm_mode_object_add+0x4c/0xbc
  Call trace:
   drm_connector_set_panel_orientation
   ili9881c_get_modes [panel_ilitek_ili9881c]

Fix this by calling drm_connector_set_orientation_from_panel() during
connector initialization, so the panel orientation property is created
before drm_dev_register().  When get_modes later calls
drm_connector_set_panel_orientation(), it finds the property already set
and returns immediately.

Signed-off-by: Seeed Studio <support@seeed.cc>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/dw-mipi-dsi2-rockchip.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/dw-mipi-dsi2-rockchip.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/dw-mipi-dsi2-rockchip.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/dw-mipi-dsi2-rockchip.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/dw-mipi-dsi2-rockchip.c
@@ -1497,6 +1497,10 @@ static int dw_mipi_dsi2_connector_init(st
 
 	drm_connector_helper_add(connector,
 				 &dw_mipi_dsi2_connector_helper_funcs);
+
+	if (dsi2->panel)
+		drm_connector_set_orientation_from_panel(connector, dsi2->panel);
+
 	ret = drm_connector_attach_encoder(connector, encoder);
 	if (ret < 0) {
 		DRM_DEV_ERROR(dev, "Failed to attach encoder: %d\n", ret);
